<h2>Project: KPI Tracking Dashboard (End-to-End)</h2>

<div class="card">
<strong>Project Overview:</strong><br>
Developed an interactive KPI Dashboard using SQL backend and Power BI frontend 
to monitor sales performance, profit margins, and target variance across 10,000+ records.
</div>

<div class="card">
<strong>SQL Database Schema:</strong>

<code>
CREATE TABLE Regions (
Region_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
Region_Name VARCHAR(50)
);
</code>

<code>
CREATE TABLE Products (
Product_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
Product_Name VARCHAR(100),
Category VARCHAR(50),
Unit_Cost DECIMAL(10,2)
);
</code>

<code>
CREATE TABLE Sales (
Sales_ID INT PRIMARY KEY,
Order_Date DATE,
Product_ID INT,
Quantity INT,
Sales_Amount DECIMAL(10,2),
FOREIGN KEY (Product_ID) REFERENCES Products(Product_ID)
);
</code>

</div>

<div class="card">
<strong>KPI SQL Query (Profit Calculation):</strong>

<code>
SELECT 
SUM(s.Sales_Amount) AS Total_Sales,
SUM(p.Unit_Cost * s.Quantity) AS Total_Cost,
SUM(s.Sales_Amount) - SUM(p.Unit_Cost * s.Quantity) AS Profit
FROM Sales s
JOIN Products p ON s.Product_ID = p.Product_ID;
</code>
</div>

<div class="card">
<strong>Power BI DAX Measures:</strong>

<code>
Total Sales = SUM(Sales[Sales_Amount])
</code>

<code>
Profit = [Total Sales] - SUMX(Sales, Sales[Quantity] * RELATED(Products[Unit_Cost]))
</code>

<code>
Profit Margin % = DIVIDE([Profit], [Total Sales], 0)
</code>
</div>

